statements: SELECT * FROM machine_learning_results;
SELECT model_name, prediction_date FROM machine_learning_results;
SELECT model_name, prediction_result FROM machine_learning_results ORDER BY prediction_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_results WHERE model_name LIKE '%logistic%';
SELECT id, model_name, prediction_date FROM machine_learning_results ORDER BY model_name ASC, prediction_date DESC;
SELECT id, model_name, prediction_result FROM machine_learning_results WHERE prediction_date = '2022-01-01';

SELECT model_name, prediction_date, prediction_result FROM machine_learning_results WHERE model_name = 'Decision Tree' AND prediction_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31' ORDER BY prediction_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_results WHERE model_name IN ('Random Forest', 'Logistic Regression') ORDER BY id ASC, prediction_date DESC;
SELECT id, model_name, prediction_result FROM machine_learning_results WHERE model_name = 'XGBoost' AND prediction_date > '2022-06-30' ORDER BY model_name, prediction_date DESC;

SELECT DISTINCT model_name, json_array_elements_text(prediction_result -> 'metrics') AS metric_name FROM machine_learning_results WHERE prediction_date > '2022-03-15' ORDER BY model_name ASC, metric_name DESC;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT model_name, model_type FROM machine_learning_models WHERE model_id = 1;
SELECT * FROM predictions WHERE prediction_date > '2022-01-01';
SELECT model_name, prediction_date, output_result FROM machine_learning_models JOIN predictions ON machine_learning_models.model_id = predictions.model_id;
SELECT model_name, COUNT(prediction_id) AS num_predictions FROM machine_learning_models INNER JOIN predictions ON machine_learning_models.model_id = predictions.model_id GROUP BY model_name;
SELECT model_name, model_type FROM machine_learning_models WHERE model_id = 1;
SELECT * FROM predictions ORDER BY prediction_date DESC;
SELECT model_name, prediction_date, input_data FROM machine_learning_models INNER JOIN predictions ON machine_learning_models.model_id = predictions.model_id;
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_models FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT DISTINCT model_type FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT * FROM model_results ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT model_name, prediction FROM model_results WHERE id = 5;
SELECT DISTINCT model_name FROM model_info;
SELECT id, input_data FROM model_predictions WHERE id < 10;
SELECT model_name, training_data FROM model_info WHERE model_name LIKE 'S%';
SELECT * FROM model_results WHERE id = 1;
SELECT model_name, prediction FROM model_results WHERE model_name = 'model1';
SELECT * FROM model_predictions WHERE id > 5 ORDER BY id DESC;
SELECT model_name, output_data FROM model_predictions WHERE model_name = 'model2' ORDER BY id ASC;
SELECT model_name, model_description FROM model_info WHERE model_name LIKE '%regression%' ORDER BY id;
SELECT * FROM model_results;
SELECT id, model_name, created_at FROM model_results ORDER BY created_at DESC;
SELECT model_name, result_json FROM model_results WHERE id = '12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789abc';
SELECT * FROM predictions WHERE created_at > NOW() - INTERVAL '1 day';
SELECT metric_name, metric_value FROM evaluation_metrics WHERE metric_value > 0.8;
SELECT * FROM model_results;
SELECT model_name, created_at FROM model_results ORDER BY created_at DESC;
SELECT model_name, result_json->'accuracy' AS accuracy FROM model_results WHERE model_name LIKE 'model_%';
SELECT p.id, p.created_at, m.model_name FROM predictions p JOIN model_results m ON p.model_id = m.id ORDER BY p.created_at ASC;

SELECT e.model_id, e.metric_name, e.metric_value, m.model_name FROM evaluation_metrics e JOIN model_results m ON e.model_id = m.id WHERE e.metric_value > 0.8 ORDER BY e.metric_value DESC, m.model_name;
SELECT * FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT id, model_name, accuracy FROM machine_learning_models;
SELECT model_name, trained_date FROM machine_learning_models ORDER BY trained_date DESC;
SELECT id, model_name, trained_date FROM machine_learning_models WHERE accuracy > 0.8;
SELECT * FROM predictions WHERE prediction_date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-06-30';
SELECT model_name, accuracy, trained_date FROM machine_learning_models WHERE accuracy > 0.8 ORDER BY trained_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM predictions WHERE result = 'Success' ORDER BY prediction_date ASC;
SELECT model_name, trained_date, accuracy, result FROM machine_learning_models JOIN predictions ON machine_learning_models.id = predictions.model_id WHERE prediction_date >= '2022-01-01';

SELECT model_name, trained_date, evaluation_date, evaluation_result FROM machine_learning_models JOIN model_evaluation ON machine_learning_models.id = model_evaluation.model_id ORDER BY evaluation_date DESC;
SELECT model_name, parameter_name, parameter_value FROM machine_learning_models JOIN model_parameters ON machine_learning_models.id = model_parameters.model_id WHERE parameter_name = 'learning_rate';
